Testicular cancer is most common in young and middle-aged men.</p>","source":"msn"}},{"title":"Noticeable skin changes","body":"<p>Men over 50 are <a href=\\"https://www.aad.org/public/diseases/skin-cancer/types/common/melanoma/men-50\\" rel=\\"noopener noreferrer\\">more likely to die from\xC2\xA0skin cancer</a>\xC2\xA0than women in the same age group; young men have a higher probability of developing deadly melanoma (the most serious skin cancer) than any other cancer,\xC2\xA0 according to the\xC2\xA0<a href=\\"https://www.skincancer.org/blog/ask-the-expert-why-are-more-men-dying-of-skin-cancer/#:~:text=Yes%2C%20skin%20cancer%20deaths%20in,in%20the%20same%20age%20group.\\" rel=\\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\\">Skin Cancer Foundation</a>.\xC2\xA0It\xE2\x80\x99s easy to miss the early warning signs of cancer in men, says\xC2\xA0<a href=\\"https://ldi.upenn.edu/fellows/fellows-directory/richard-c-wender-md/\\" rel=\\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\\">Richard Wender</a>, MD, former chief cancer control officer for the American Cancer Society. \xE2\x80\x9CMany people think freckles, moles, or a darker age spot is just like the others they\xE2\x80\x99ve had,\xE2\x80\x9D he explains. If you notice a mole getting darker, larger, or becoming raised, get it checked. With melanoma, spots are often irregularly shaped (not round), significantly darker in colour, or even two distinctly different colours within one spot, he says. \xE2\x80\x9CMelanoma is far less common than other skin cancers, but has the potential to be more deadly,\xE2\x80\x9D says Dr. Wender. \xE2\x80\x9CHowever, many melanomas have a long period where they\xE2\x80\x99re not invasive and easy to cure, as long as they\xE2\x80\x99re caught early.\xE2\x80\x9D</p> <p>Here are the <a href=\\"https://www.readersdigest.ca/health/conditions/tell-difference-skin-conditions/\\">skin changes you should never ignore</a>.</p>","image":{"width":1000,"height":750,"quality":81,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAWmYVy.img","attribution":"Photo: Shutterstock","title":"Noticeable skin changes","caption":"<p>Men over 50 are about twice as likely as women to develop and die from skin cancer; young men account for 40 per cent of melanoma cases, but 60 per cent of melanoma deaths, according to the Skin Cancer Foundation. Why? A study by the National Sun Protection Advisory Council found that men spend more time in the sun than women and are less likely to wear sunscreen; men also have less hair covering their scalp and ears, two areas where they tend to develop cancer. Also, traditionally men visit the doctor less often than women do, so their cancers may not be caught as early.</p> <p>It's easy to miss the early warning signs of skin cancer, says Rich Wender, MD, chief cancer control officer for the American Cancer Society. \xE2\x80\x9CMany people think freckles, moles, or\xC2\xA0darker age spots are just like the others they\xE2\x80\x99ve had,\xE2\x80\x9D he explains. dinner.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/foodanddrink/recipes/35-delicious-healthy-lunch-recipes-for-weight-loss/ss-AA14KJm0","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"body":"<p>When it\xE2\x80\x99s midday and you realize your stomach is already growling, the last thing you want to do is find a place to get a healthful meal. You\xE2\x80\x99re hungry, and it\xE2\x80\x99s just so convenient to head to the office cafeteria for whatever they have to offer. But if your goal is losing weight, planning healthy lunch ideas for <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/weight-loss/diets/g20440614/25-best-weight-loss-tips-ever/\\">weight loss</a> to have at the ready makes the biggest difference in supporting your goals.</p><p>And skipping out on lunch is never an option. \xE2\x80\x9CIt\xE2\x80\x99s unfair to expect our body or brain to perform at their best if we aren\xE2\x80\x99t providing the fuel they need through food,\xE2\x80\x9D says <a href=\\"https://streetsmartnutrition.com/about/\\">Cara Harbstreet, M.S., R.D., L.D.</a>, owner of <a href=\\"http://www.streetsmartnutrition.com\\">Street Smart Nutrition</a>. \xE2\x80\x9CSkipping a mid-day meal eliminates a key opportunity to get essential nutrition or food groups that may not show up in other meals or snacks.\xE2\x80\x9D </p><h2>How to build a healthy lunch for weight loss</h2><p>The most important thing to keep in mind when planning your lunches for the week is choosing foods that taste good to you, make you feel good, and keep you satisfied, says <a href=\\"https://beautifuleatsandthings.com/about/\\">Andrea Mathis, M.A., R.D.N., L.D.N.</a>, author of <a href=\\"https://www.amazon.com/Complete-Book-Smoothies-Healthy-Energize-ebook/dp/B091MDL2J5?tag=syndication-20&ascsubtag=%5Bartid%7C2141.g.42100898%5Bsrc%7Cmsn-us\\"><em>The Complete Book of Smoothies</em></a>. Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. Your plate should include fiber, fat, and protein to promote the feeling of fullness and manage appetite. One of her favorite ingredients to incorporate into meals is avocados, which have heart-healthy fats and fiber to keep you satisfied. <br>And if you\xE2\x80\x99re struggling with planning lunches that help you reach your goals, Mathis encourages setting realistic and sustainable goals for yourself. \xE2\x80\x9CTo help you stay on track, choose meals that are easy to prepare and set aside a time or day to prep your meals,\xE2\x80\x9D she says. Harbstreet adds that you can try \xE2\x80\x9Chabit stacking\xE2\x80\x9D which includes attaching <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/food-nutrition/a20472042/6-protein-packed-meal-prep-recipes/\\">meal prep</a> to a habit you already have. For example, you could prep your lunch as soon as you get home instead of waiting for later when you\xE2\x80\x99d rather be relaxing, she suggests.<br>Ready to get cooking? Here are 35 of our favorite lunch ideas for <a href=\\"https://www.prevention.com/weight-loss/diets/g29462611/best-diets-weight-loss/\\">weight loss</a> that you can incorporate into your meal prep routine ASAP.</p>","image":{"width":2560,"height":1280,"quality":79,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA14Kxc0.img","attribution":"Prevention","title":"35 Delicious, Healthy Lunch Recipes for Weight Loss","caption":"<p>When it\xE2\x80\x99s midday and you realize your stomach is already growling, the last thing you want to do is find a place to get a healthful meal. Without that, you won\xE2\x80\x99t enjoy or look forward to your meals and you\xE2\x80\x99re more likely to snack throughout the day.Additionally, choose foods that are nutrient-dense and support your health goals, Mathis says. //prod-streaming-video-msn-com.akamaized.net/df870e12-455d-4fae-ac39-934554eea13d/c8735ed0-d3db-4413-aafd-08c4622d_650.mp4","width":204,"height":360,"contentType":"video/mp4","fileSize":10993464}],"publishedDateTime":"2023-04-14T15:34:11Z","isFeatured":false,"images":[{"width":1920,"height":1000,"quality":89,"url":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA19RRln.img","attribution":"Provided by BuzzVideos","title":"Baby Tries To Trick Parent That He's Still Asleep","source":"msn","colorSamples":[{"isDarkMode":true,"hexColor":"#2f3f2e","isGreyScale":false},{"isDarkMode":false,"hexColor":"#e9ebc1","isGreyScale":false}]}],"colorSamples":[{"isDarkMode":true,"hexColor":"#2f3f2e","secHexColor":"#3d3c2e","gradientAngle":"135deg","isGreyScale":false},{"isDarkMode":false,"hexColor":"#e9ebc1","secHexColor":"#efe7e0","gradientAngle":"135deg","isGreyScale":false}],"provider":{"id":"AAm31QF","name":"BuzzVideos","logoUrl":"https://img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/BBAp9C5.img","profileId":"vid-d82k8xp5kkcntdq6ivkrwi8bv5nby02ugaaa2tkg2ew42q6mh6bs"},"category":"video","reactionSummary":{"totalCount":168,"subReactionSummaries":[{"totalCount":149,"type":"upvote"},{"totalCount":19,"type":"downvote"}]},"reactionStatus":"on","commentSummary":{"totalCount":6,"subCommentSummaries":[{"totalCount":6,"type":"comment"}]},"commentStatus":"on","feed":{"feedName":"news","lastFreActionTimestamp":0},"isWorkNewsContent":false,"reasons":[{"type":"interacted","rank":0}],"recoId":"ePaCTRA1qaXz0qBk0vxGCbJwwa","size":0,"isDynamicCard":false},{"id":"AA19SASI","type":"slideshow","title":"Taking Zyrtec All The Time For Your Allergies Can Come With Some Side Effects","abstract":"They're rare but still sucky. Spring can seem synonymous with warmer weather and more sunshine. But it's also a time when many people are coughing, sneezing, and blowing your nose nonstop. Allergy meds like Zyrtec can alleviate some of your symptoms. As with any other drugs, it's important to keep Zyrtec side effects in mind so you can get all the benefits while minimizing any potential downsides. The good news is there are fewer side effects from Zyrtec compared to first-generation antihistamines such as Benadryl, and it's relatively safe even at higher than standard doses for most people, says Jennifer Toh, MD, an allergist and immunologist at ENT and Allergy Associates. Plus, any side effects are typically mild, and a majority of people can take the medication with no issues, says Purvi Parikh, MD, an allergist and immunologist at Allergy & Asthma Network. ICYMI, Zyrtec is an antihistamine and it blocks histamines to stop allergic reactions, says Virginia Boomershine, an ambulatory clinical pharmacy regional senior manager for Banner Pharmacy Services. Histamines are the culprits behind all those pesky allergy symptoms, like itchy, watery eyes, runny nose, scratchy throat, and sneezing. Keep reading to find out whether this medication is right for you and what you can do about the potential side effects. Meet the experts: Jennifer Toh, MD, is an allergist and immunologist at ENT and Allergy Associates. Purvi Parikh, MD, is an allergist and immunologist at Allergy & Asthma Network. Virginia Boomershine is an ambulatory clinical pharmacy regional senior manager for Banner Pharmacy Services Is it safe to take Zyrtec every day? Yep. \\"When taken in the recommended doses, antihistamines can be taken daily. This is especially true with Zyrtec, since it doesn't show decreasing effectiveness if used daily,\\" says Sima Patel, MD, an allergist at New York Allergy & Sinus Centers. Still, it's probably worth holding off on medication that you don't need, says Dr. Patel. So if you aren't having allergy symptoms or they get milder during a certain time of the year, that's probably a good time to take a Zyrtec break. \\"We always want the least amount of medication to control symptoms. However, starting allergy medications two weeks prior to your symptomatic season is best to help prevent symptoms,\\" Dr. Patel says. Is it better to take Zyrtec in the morning or at night? It depends on whether you experience any side effects, says Robert Eitches, MD, an allergist at Tower Allergy. If your problems are only during the day time and you aren't really prone to side effects, then go ahead and take it during the day. But if you experience side effects like drowsiness, Dr. Eitches recommends taking your dose at night before bed. \\"That way you wake up in the morning relatively clearer too,\\" he says. If it makes you sleepy, the side effect will have likely worn off by the time you wake up, and since the medication can provide relief for 24 hours, you'll still experience relief during the day. Is there anyone who should not take Zyrtec? Zyrtec is safe for most people, but there are some individuals who should stay away. Children under 2, anyone with a history of an allergic reaction to Zyrtec or hydroxyzine/piperazine derivatives, and those with severe renal impairment shouldn't take Zyrtec, says Dr. Patel. If you are pregnant and breastfeeding, Dr. Patel recommends speaking to your doctor before using it. The medication is \\"primarily eliminated from your body through the kidneys,\\" says Dr. Parikh. So, if your kidneys aren't functioning properly, the medication can accumulate and build up in your blood, which may cause additional damage to your kidneys and severe side effects. Additionally, if you take any medications that can cause sedation, such as benzodiazepines, you should talk with your doctor before taking Zyrtec, says Dr. Parikh, because combining the two may cause worsened side effects. Other antihistamines are typically okay to take with Zyrtec as long as they don\xE2\x80\x99t make you too sleepy, she adds. And it's always a good idea avoid alcohol when you're on Zyrtec. When in doubt, go to your doctor with any questions before you take Zyrtec to quell allergy symptoms. 10 Zyrtec Side Effects To Be Aware Of It's best to be aware of potential Zyrtec side effects\xE2\x80\x94especially if you're planning on popping the stuff on the reg over the next few months.","url":"https://www.msn.com/en-ca/health/medical/taking-zyrtec-all-the-time-for-your-allergies-can-come-with-some-side-effects/ss-AA19SASI","locale":"en-us","isLocalContent":false,"galleryItemCount":0,"slides":[{"title":"1) Drowsiness","body":"<p>If you've ever slept 14 hours after popping a Benadryl, you're well aware that some allergy meds can seriously knock you out.
